TS GALAXY goalkeeper Melusi Buthelezi became a victim of car hijacking in Soweto early evening on Saturday. The club confirmed on Sunday afterrnoon that the goal minder was admitted to hospital in stable condition after being stabbed in a hijacking incident in Soweto.  "Buthelezi and his brother were returning from visiting their ailing mother when they were cornered by car hijackers at a petrol filling station in Soweto. They both suffered stab wounds and were admitted to the hospital. Buthelezi is in a stable condition even though his brother is said to be critical," the club statement said. "His family has asked for privacy while they are trying to deal with this unforeseen circumstance. TS Galaxy is appealing to the masses to afford Buthelezi and his family privacy during these trying times." The 23-year-old made his PSL debut in the Nedbank Cup 1-0 win against Kaizer Chiefs a fortnight ago. Since then he has kept two consecutive clean sheets in the Dstv Premiership matches against Swallows and Amazulu.  